 Power BI Implementation

 1. Donut Chart (Movies vs TV Shows)
- Initial Setup:
  - Select Donut Chart visualization
  - Add Type to Legend
  - Add Count of Type to Values

- Format:
  - Configure data labels
  - Set custom colors
  - Add title

 2. Area Chart (Releases by Year)
- Create Visual:
  - Select Area Chart
  - Add Release Year to X-Axis
  - Add Number of Records to Y-Axis
  - Add Type to Legend

- Format:
  - Adjust axes
  - Set colors
  - Add title

 3. Horizontal Bar Chart (Top 10 Genres)
- Base Setup:
  - Select Clustered Bar Chart
  - Add Genre to Y-Axis
  - Add Number of Records to X-Axis

- Configure:
  - Set Top N filter for genres
  - Adjust sorting

- Format:
  - Set colors
  - Adjust bar styles
  - Add title

 4. Map (Shows by Country)
- Create Map:
  - Select Map visual
  - Add Country to Location
  - Add Number of Records to Size and Color

- Format:
  - Set map style
  - Adjust data colors
  - Configure tooltips

 5. Text Visualization (Movie Descriptions)
- Setup:
  - Add Card visual
  - Add Description to Values

- Add Controls:
  - Create Title slicer
  - Configure selection behavior

- Format:
  - Adjust font properties
  - Set card size
  - Add title

 6. Interactive Dashboard
- Layout:
  - Arrange all visuals
  - Add slicers for filtering

- Configure Interactions:
  - Set visual interactions
  - Configure filtering behavior

- Final Format:
  - Add dashboard title
  - Adjust layout
  - Set visual themes
  - Prepare for publishing
